A ministerial meeting of Africa's lumber producers is set to take place in Cabinda, Angola, to discuss new policies for lumber imports and exports.
The African Timber Organization will host the 17th Africa Timber Conference in Cabinda, focusing on conservation of tropical rainforests.
Angola's Deputy Minister of Agriculture announced the agenda, which includes protecting gibbons, vital indicators of rainforest health.
Malaysia and Austria will collaborate on remote sensing satellites to monitor tropical forests.
Efforts to combat deforestation and land degradation in Africa are also underway, emphasizing the importance of environmental conservation and sustainable practices.
